---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import ContentSection from '@components/ContentSection.astro';
import DesignProblemIcon from '@assets/design-problem-flat.svg';
import ImageFigure from '@/components/ImageFigure.astro';
import EngageLogo from '@assets/engage-logo.png';
import SelTest from '@assets/sel.png';
---

<ContentSection>
    <DesignProblemIcon
        slot="icon"
        style="--icon-subject-color: var(--color-neutral-100); --icon-field-color: var(--color-secondary-500);"
    />

    <div slot="title" class="pb-8">Design Challenge</div>
    <div slot="content">
        <p class="mb-4">
            Staff working on this national biomedical research program are
            regularly asked <span class="font-bold text-secondary-500"
                >complex, highly technical questions</span
            > by members of the public. These questions often touch on genetics,
            data privacy, research ethics, and medical terminology. To respond accurately,
            staff must not only remember the correct information, they must interpret
            it, adapt it to context, and <span
                class="font-bold text-secondary-500"
                >explain it clearly at a wide range of literacy levels</span
            >. The existing training approach relied almost entirely on written
            resources, especially model respenses to frequently asked questions.
        </p>
        <div class="mx-2 my-4 leading-6.5">
            <span
                class="font-bold rounded-md py-1 px-1 text-foreground-light bg-linear-to-r from-secondary-500 to-primary-400 tracking-wide"
                style=" box-decoration-break: clone"
            >
                There was no structured way for staff to practice forming
                responses and receive meaningful feedback.
            </span>
        </div>

        <div slot="read-more">
            <p class="mb-4 break-inside-avoid-column">
                When staff did practice, the feedback was often:
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside my-3">
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-bold">Inconsistent</span>, depending
                        on who reviewed it
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-bold">Delayed</span>, arriving after
                        the moment of need
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-bold">Difficult to scale</span>,
                        especially across distributed teams
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>

            <p class="mb-4">
                <span class="font-bold text-secondary-500"
                    >Yet the stakes were high.</span
                > Responses must be:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside my-3">
                <li>
                    <span class="font-bold">Accurate and complete</span> to maintain
                    public trust and comply with research guidelines
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="font-bold">Consistent</span> across the nation-wide
                    organization
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="font-bold">Supportive and understandable</span
                    >, regardless of the learnerâ€™s technical background
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mb-4">
                In short, we needed a way to provide scalable, individualized
                feedback that <span class="font-bold text-secondary-500"
                    >helps staff learn to communicate complex information
                    confidently and responsibly</span
                >.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</ContentSection>
